The paper deals with topic modeling, which is a subfield of machine learning and natural language processing. The paper discusses the necessary and sufficient conditions for consistent separable topic estimation, which involves statistical and information-theoretic concepts. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
